DataElement.preferredName: Non-Protocol Therapeutic Procedure Tyrosine Kinase Inhibitor Administered Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElement.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator related to the administration of a non-protocol tyrosine kinase inhibitor therapy, any substance that inhibits tyrosine kinase, an enzyme involved in the transduction and processing of many extracellular and intracellular signals including cell proliferation. Inhibition of tyrosine kinase may result in inhibition of cell growth and cell proliferation.
